---
description: All user-facing and developer-facing text must be in English only
alwaysApply: true
---

# English-only text

Until multilingual support is explicitly added, use **English only** for:

- UI strings, labels, placeholders, button text, and toasts
- Error messages, validation messages, and API response messages intended for humans
- README, inline documentation in code, and commit/PR descriptions when you author them for this repo
- **Code comments** (including `//`, `/* */`, docstrings, and JSX `{/* */}` comments)

Do not use other natural languages in source, config comments, or generated copy. If you encounter existing non-English text while editing, prefer translating it to English as part of the same change when it is clearly user- or maintainer-facing.

Technical identifiers (variable names, routes, locale keys) stay as conventional English or existing project naming; this rule is about human-readable prose and comments.
